00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:31,067
- Go get her!
- I don’t want to get involved!

255
00:13:31,317 --> 00:13:32,442
Ah, here we go!

256
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:36,550
Iskineport!

257
00:13:36,738 --> 00:13:37,738
Run!

258
00:13:37,937 --> 00:13:40,164
Go to the police
and report this! Fast!

259
00:13:40,188 --> 00:13:41,522
- Thank you, thank you!
- Let go of me!

260
00:13:45,615 --> 00:13:46,615
I’m the police!

261
00:13:46,615 --> 00:13:50,263
He’s the snatcher!

262
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:51,450
Oh, chief

263
00:13:51,864 --> 00:13:52,864
run after him, then!

264
00:13:52,864 --> 00:13:54,840
There really are a lot
of thieves in the area

265
00:13:54,864 --> 00:13:55,864
Yes!

266
00:13:56,864 --> 00:13:59,032
Go ahead! Get all the criminals!

267
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,824
Thank you, thank you.

268
00:14:01,864 --> 00:14:03,864
You’re really great kids,
Tash, Andres!

269
00:14:04,074 --> 00:14:07,480
You really are going to sacrifice your
careers to help your bakery business.

270
00:14:07,505 --> 00:14:09,050
Of course,
but we’re going back to Singapore

271
00:14:09,074 --> 00:14:11,883
when all is settled in Dad’s bakery.

272
00:14:11,908 --> 00:14:15,054
But you know what, actually, you’re not
the only store who’s barely making enough.

273
00:14:15,469 --> 00:14:17,008
Boss Beauty and my store, too!

274
00:14:17,032 --> 00:14:19,133
- It’s true.
- All stores here

275
00:14:19,157 --> 00:14:20,800
- Actually.
- aren’t making enough.

276
00:14:20,824 --> 00:14:25,864
What we need is something to jumpstart and
make some noise for the businesses here!

277
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:27,948
- Orb!
- How are you?

278
00:14:28,452 --> 00:14:33,639
Remember last week I told you a lot
of our classmates are crushing on you?

279
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:34,664
Yeah, why?

280
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:38,865
A lot of them are sending
pick-up lines for you.

281
00:14:39,032 --> 00:14:41,091
Really?
Let me hear some of them!

282
00:14:41,115 --> 00:14:42,864
Are you not getting tired, Andres?

283
00:14:43,409 --> 00:14:44,409
Why?

284
00:14:44,434 --> 00:14:47,309
You’ve been running
in my mind, non stop!

285
00:14:52,864 --> 00:14:54,467
That’s flattering!

286
00:14:54,491 --> 00:14:55,800
Correct!

287
00:14:55,824 --> 00:14:57,258
- One more?
- Okay, okay, one more!

288
00:14:57,282 --> 00:14:58,676
Let me hear one more!

289
00:14:58,683 --> 00:14:59,840
Okay, okay!

290
00:14:59,864 --> 00:15:01,282
- Are you an examination?
- Why?

291
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:03,710
I want to.. answer you.

292
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:11,686
Guys, I will die of flattery!

293
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:13,686
You know what,
you too look good together!

294
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:14,920
Super good!

295
00:15:16,710 --> 00:15:19,170
Eew, yuck! Us two?

296
00:15:19,587 --> 00:15:20,710
How about the two of us, then?

297
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,014
This is my bro! Orb!

298
00:15:22,039 --> 00:15:24,104
Yeah, he’s my broski!

299
00:15:24,128 --> 00:15:25,295
Bestest friend!

300
00:15:25,545 --> 00:15:26,670
That’s it!

301
00:15:26,710 --> 00:15:27,710
OMG!

302
00:15:28,337 --> 00:15:29,337
That’s it, guys!

303
00:15:29,378 --> 00:15:31,397
I have an idea!

304
00:15:31,710 --> 00:15:33,729
You guys are gonna love this, promise!

305
00:15:33,753 --> 00:15:34,878
- What is it?
- What, what?

306
00:15:35,462 --> 00:15:37,003
Food bazaar!

307
00:15:38,503 --> 00:15:40,710
Food bazaar!

308
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:44,710
You know what, my love?

309
00:15:45,331 --> 00:15:47,206
I’m excited for our date later.

310
00:15:47,710 --> 00:15:51,271
I put in a reservation at Mema Mall,
and we'll watch a movie.

311
00:15:51,295 --> 00:15:52,295
Wow!

312
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:56,686
That’s why I’m rushing through
this pasta and cake for our neighbors!

313
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:59,354
Andres, you handle
giving this away, okay?

314
00:15:59,378 --> 00:16:01,961
And of course,
don’t forget Chef K!

315
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:04,963
Okay!

316
00:16:06,537 --> 00:16:07,537
You know what, Andres,

317
00:16:08,537 --> 00:16:12,140
I noticed.
You look like you can’t stay put.

318
00:16:12,165 --> 00:16:13,165
Dad,

319
00:16:13,356 --> 00:16:17,065
can we move your meet-up
anniversary for one day?

320
00:16:17,702 --> 00:16:18,819
- Why?
- Your celebration.

321
00:16:19,052 --> 00:16:20,934
- Why?
- Because...

322
00:16:20,959 --> 00:16:24,495
Tasha and I have decided that
we’re going to have a food bazaar.

323
00:16:25,301 --> 00:16:26,342
Can you help us tonight?

324
00:16:27,269 --> 00:16:28,561
Wait, what?

325
00:16:28,702 --> 00:16:31,579
A bazaar? With a lot of people?

326
00:16:31,702 --> 00:16:33,678
Yes, Lola Maxi, exactly!

327
00:16:33,901 --> 00:16:35,194
Aside from our bakery,

328
00:16:35,502 --> 00:16:39,294
we’ll try to get more exposure for
the other businesses in our community.

329
00:16:39,702 --> 00:16:40,995
Hang on, give me a second.

330
00:16:42,135 --> 00:16:45,677
Here we go again. So, you guys
decided again without my prior knowledge?

331
00:16:45,702 --> 00:16:47,702
And then this is for tomorrow?

332
00:16:48,329 --> 00:16:49,702
What are you selling?

333
00:16:50,293 --> 00:16:51,293
Cookies, Dad!

334
00:16:51,702 --> 00:16:54,380
- Cookies?
- With additional gimik!

335
00:16:54,537 --> 00:16:59,702
Nothing too fancy, but enough to
generate curiosity among the gen z!

336
00:16:59,953 --> 00:17:07,702
Okay, your dad and I will move our
celebration to support you and Atasha.

337
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:13,399
I’ll help you bake
the cookies! Okay?

338
00:17:13,454 --> 00:17:17,870
That sounds great, Dad!
Thank you!

339
00:17:18,702 --> 00:17:20,702
- Thank you!
- Kiss!

340
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:22,755
I love you, Dad! Mwah!

341
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:23,870
I love you too!

342
00:17:25,370 --> 00:17:26,370
Lola Maxi!

343
00:17:26,895 --> 00:17:30,647
Lola Maxi, what are you doing?
You’re not supposed to be eating icing!

344
00:17:30,672 --> 00:17:33,648
That’s too sweet!

345
00:17:33,673 --> 00:17:35,550
You guys are too much!

346
00:17:38,662 --> 00:17:41,662
I don’t like eating icing!

347
00:17:41,985 --> 00:17:44,652
Oh, sorry, Lola Maxi,
I guess we were wrong!

348
00:17:44,912 --> 00:17:46,203
You’re all too much!

349
00:17:48,562 --> 00:17:52,242
Andres, how did you
learn to bake cookies?

350
00:17:52,490 --> 00:17:54,823
We were always here
when we were young.

351
00:17:55,961 --> 00:17:58,045
Okay, so what’s the gimik?

352
00:17:58,605 --> 00:18:00,880
Dad, relax, it’s a surprise!

353
00:18:01,454 --> 00:18:02,454
You’ll find out tomorrow.

354
00:18:02,870 --> 00:18:04,846
- Just do this for now!
- Are you sure I will be surprised?

355
00:18:04,870 --> 00:18:07,970
Of course! We got you!
Tasha and I.

356
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:09,167
Just, do this!

357
00:18:09,537 --> 00:18:10,678
- Okay, then!
- Yeah!

358
00:18:10,702 --> 00:18:11,702
Here I go!

359
00:18:12,702 --> 00:18:17,555
Okay, we almost have a hundred
calling cards for Bake Haus of U!

360
00:18:17,579 --> 00:18:18,579
Are these enough?

361
00:18:18,702 --> 00:18:19,702
Yes!

362
00:18:19,702 --> 00:18:21,678
So that anytime someone passes by,

363
00:18:21,702 --> 00:18:23,513
they can get one from the table,

364
00:18:23,537 --> 00:18:28,305
so they have our contact number just in
case they want to order from us next time.

365
00:18:28,329 --> 00:18:29,329
Right!

366
00:18:29,537 --> 00:18:32,579
Wait, what are we
doing these for?

367
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:35,329
It’s for the food bazaar, Lola.

368
00:18:35,702 --> 00:18:40,454
So we can promote the bakery and the
other businesses here in the barangay.

369
00:18:41,702 --> 00:18:44,156
What are you up to there, Atasha?

370
00:18:44,537 --> 00:18:47,193
Oh, a social media page?!

371
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:51,470
Yes! This is the social media
page for Barangay Cinco,

372
00:18:51,495 --> 00:18:53,430
so tomorrow, we can go
on live during the bazaar,

373
00:18:53,454 --> 00:18:56,740
so we get a lot more
exposure for the businesses.

374
00:18:56,765 --> 00:18:58,006
See here, look!

375
00:18:58,031 --> 00:18:59,662
Wow, thank you.

376
00:18:59,703 --> 00:19:06,702
To you and Andres, for not just helping
us but for helping also our community.

377
00:19:07,103 --> 00:19:08,103
Of course, mom!

378
00:19:08,630 --> 00:19:11,236
Wherelse did we learn
this from but you and Dad.

379
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:14,833
Just like Dad always say,
we’re one big family here.

380
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:21,601
But wait, where did the
bazaar idea come from, hija?

381
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:23,766
Lola, we need to be quick here.

382
00:19:23,790 --> 00:19:26,958
There are a lot
of mariteses here.

383
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,542
They might catch wind
and copy our idea!

384
00:19:29,790 --> 00:19:34,083
The fast ones really outdo
the hardworking ones.

385
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:36,393
What do you mean?

386
00:19:36,417 --> 00:19:41,601
That’s what I loved
about your Lolo Roman.

387
00:19:42,064 --> 00:19:44,647
He’s one of a kind!

388
00:19:44,672 --> 00:19:48,441
On our first date, he
brought me to the cinema!

389
00:19:48,583 --> 00:19:52,601
He got my by being speedy!

390
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:54,750
Mom?! Oh my god!

391
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:59,790
In the dark cinema?
Oh, my goodness!

392
00:19:59,815 --> 00:20:02,767
Lola, wait up! Tasha is here!

393
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,267
Lola, stop!

394
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:07,766
It was cold! The AC was cold!

395
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:10,208
Your Lolo’s hand

396
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:13,518
Lola! Lolo’s hands what?!

397
00:20:13,542 --> 00:20:14,790
Well

398
00:20:18,790 --> 00:20:21,184
Gosh, we’ve been working
on this bazaar overnight!

399
00:20:21,208 --> 00:20:23,434
My beauty is overwhelmed!

400
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:24,458
True!

401
00:20:24,483 --> 00:20:26,766
Tash and Andres
really thought of this well!

402
00:20:26,790 --> 00:20:29,958
They still thought to help us!

403
00:20:29,983 --> 00:20:31,359
Exactly!

404
00:20:31,551 --> 00:20:33,966
You know what, it all boils down
to how they were brought up!

405
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:35,902
That’s why I really
salute Aga and Cha.

406
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:40,434
When I get pregnant,
I’ll make sure to be so close to them!

407
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:41,766
You’re going to get pregnant?!

408
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:43,790
Anne, nothing is
impossible today!

409
00:20:44,417 --> 00:20:45,790
- There is!
- In six months?

410
00:20:46,458 --> 00:20:47,790
There is!

411
00:20:48,041 --> 00:20:49,667
What you’re doing is impossible!

412
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:50,790
Anne!

413
00:20:51,245 --> 00:20:53,430
Did I tell you to join
this food bazaar?

414
00:20:53,574 --> 00:20:55,157
I’m just helping out!

415
00:20:55,696 --> 00:21:00,225
Ah, Chef K, what’s impossible
for the food bazaar?

416
00:21:00,790 --> 00:21:02,874
What you’re doing is!

417
00:21:03,542 --> 00:21:06,790
It’s not like sales will soar high
because of that bazaar!

418
00:21:07,649 --> 00:21:11,036
You should be supporting
my bakery, Beki Naman!

419
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:14,766
Because my breads are better!

420
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:16,766
And those sell well!

421
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,434
Tiyo K, we barely sell.

422
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:20,208
Stop talking,
I’m not talking to you!

423
00:21:20,625 --> 00:21:25,041
Tash and Andres said,
all businesses are now on social media.

424
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:30,166
A lot more customers will
be able to see our promos.

425
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:34,790
How will you make sale,
when the people pay online?

426
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:36,790
You won’t profit there!

427
00:21:37,307 --> 00:21:39,890
Chef K, you can use a QR Code.

428
00:21:39,958 --> 00:21:41,142
That’s one more thing!

429
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:42,601
QR Code? What is that?

430
00:21:42,625 --> 00:21:44,184
Mariposa, get the scanner!

431
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:45,291
Okay!

432
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,142
Okay!

433
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:49,601
Chef K, this is a QR code.

434
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:51,559
Put it up a little
higher so we can scan.

435
00:21:51,583 --> 00:21:55,142
When they buy online, all they need to do
is scan, and then tada!

436
00:21:55,166 --> 00:21:56,417
They’re paid!

437
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,058
You wanna take a good look?

438
00:21:59,083 --> 00:22:01,250
Raisins! What the heck!

439
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:02,667
Will you stop!

440
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:06,017
I don’t like it!
I like cash transactions better!

441
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:09,142
It’s more profitable there,
direct payments!

442
00:22:09,166 --> 00:22:10,542
You get paid immediately.

443
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:11,833
Right, kap?!

444
00:22:12,667 --> 00:22:13,790
Remember our agreement?

445
00:22:14,474 --> 00:22:16,307
Don’t give them a permit.

446
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:20,375
They’re on the sides, they’re not
bothering anyone! There’s more space!

447
00:22:20,703 --> 00:22:22,703
When was your last
deposit again?

448
00:22:23,046 --> 00:22:26,046
I think you owe me more now!
Like fifty thousand!

449
00:22:26,417 --> 00:22:27,790
- Fifty thousand?
- Yes!

450
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:29,790
So I repeat,

451
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:32,000
do not give them a permit!

452
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:39,153
If you do, that fifty thousand you owe me,
you have to pay in full with interest!

453
00:22:39,889 --> 00:22:40,889
You understand?!

454
00:22:41,603 --> 00:22:42,603
Yes, yes!

455
00:22:43,375 --> 00:22:44,790
You frustrate me!

456
00:22:47,208 --> 00:22:48,208
Move!

457
00:22:52,208 --> 00:22:53,766
I didn’t know you love cookies.

458
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:54,790
Of course, look!

459
00:22:54,815 --> 00:22:56,648
Of course, that’s the Pers family!

460
00:22:56,673 --> 00:22:57,673
Hey!

461
00:22:57,790 --> 00:22:59,000
Look, this one has writing on it!

462
00:22:59,208 --> 00:23:06,142
Andres, I noticed last night,
why are your cookies so wide?

463
00:23:06,166 --> 00:23:08,393
- Look at it!
- Remember, Dad, remember.

464
00:23:08,417 --> 00:23:12,208
I told you just wait and see.

465
00:23:12,542 --> 00:23:14,766
- Wait and see?
- Just wait and see.

466
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:17,766
Kuya, you’re the father!

467
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,767
You should know
what they’re up to!

468
00:23:19,791 --> 00:23:23,041
Look at me, I live in your
house and oh, my goodness!

469
00:23:23,208 --> 00:23:24,393
What are they up to?

470
00:23:24,417 --> 00:23:25,790
What’s their surprise?

471
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:29,043
I have no idea!

472
00:23:29,068 --> 00:23:32,642
See, you know nothing!
You have a lot to say.

473
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:34,142
What did Andres say?
What’s the gimik?

474
00:23:34,166 --> 00:23:36,458
I’ve been saying the
cookies are too wide!

475
00:23:36,667 --> 00:23:37,667
Gosh!

476
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:39,766
Oh, you talk?

477
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:42,059
I thought you were a vegetable.

478
00:23:42,083 --> 00:23:44,458
You will be surprised
with our gimik!

479
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:47,766
I tell you!

480
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:50,396
Huh?! We don’t have
the captain’s permit?!

481
00:23:50,493 --> 00:23:51,493
Unfortunately not.

482
00:23:51,790 --> 00:23:52,790
What’s gonna happen now?

483
00:23:53,250 --> 00:23:56,625
Please don’t tell me we wasted
our time and effort on this!

484
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:58,250
Look at the decorations!

485
00:23:58,533 --> 00:24:01,674
Everything was put
together for today!

486
00:24:01,698 --> 00:24:03,674
Tash, calm down, calm down!
Let’s not panic, okay?

487
00:24:03,698 --> 00:24:04,960
- Calm down.
- You know what,

488
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:08,050
let’s just think of a way to
push through with the bazaar.

489
00:24:08,074 --> 00:24:09,074
Okay?

490
00:24:09,099 --> 00:24:11,674
Hang on, I thought of something.

491
00:24:11,698 --> 00:24:12,698
What?

492
00:24:16,045 --> 00:24:17,045
Game?

493
00:24:17,724 --> 00:24:18,724
What’s the idea?

494
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:19,870
Call!

495
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,260
Why did you put these up,
you don’t have a permit!

496
00:24:24,325 --> 00:24:25,325
Cap?

497
00:24:25,817 --> 00:24:28,444
Even if I kiss you on the lips?

498
00:24:29,908 --> 00:24:31,478
- Really?
- Cap,

499
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:32,717
you better think fast
before I change my mind.

500
00:24:32,853 --> 00:24:34,786
- You're too slow!
- Ah, yes, Cap!

501
00:24:35,341 --> 00:24:37,341
Mariposa’s kiss
is one of a kind!

502
00:24:37,366 --> 00:24:38,674
I’ll go ahead,
he’s taking too long to decide!

503
00:24:38,698 --> 00:24:41,674
Wait, wait! Can I have

504
00:24:41,698 --> 00:24:42,884
three kisses? Please?

505
00:24:42,908 --> 00:24:44,674
Um, wait. Let me think about it.

506
00:24:44,698 --> 00:24:45,698
Come on!

507
00:24:45,991 --> 00:24:49,674
Okay, Cap!
Since I like you, three kisses!

508
00:24:49,698 --> 00:24:51,967
- Okay!
- But, Cap, wait!

509
00:24:51,991 --> 00:24:56,467
